# Home Decor Affiliate Blog - Cursor Rules

## Project Overview
This is a modern, SEO-optimized affiliate blog website for the home decor niche. The project uses Next.js 14 with TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, and follows best practices for performance, SEO, and user experience.

## Tech Stack
- **Framework**: Next.js 14 (App Router)
- **Language**: TypeScript
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS
- **SEO**: next-seo
- **Deployment**: Vercel-ready

## Code Style & Best Practices

### General
- Use TypeScript for all components and utilities
- Follow React best practices (functional components, hooks)
- Use meaningful variable and function names
- Add JSDoc comments for complex functions
- Keep components small and focused (single responsibility)
- Use Next.js App Router conventions

### File Structure
```
/app
  /(routes) - Route groups
  /api - API routes
/components
  /ui - Reusable UI components
  /layout - Layout components
  /blog - Blog-specific components
/lib - Utilities and helpers
/types - TypeScript type definitions
/public - Static assets
```

### Component Guidelines
- Use functional components with TypeScript
- Extract reusable logic into custom hooks
- Use composition over inheritance
- Keep components under 200 lines when possible
- Use proper prop types with TypeScript interfaces
- Implement proper error boundaries

### Styling
- Use Tailwind CSS utility classes
- Create reusable component classes when needed
- Use CSS variables for theme colors
- Ensure responsive design (mobile-first approach)
- Use semantic HTML elements
- Maintain consistent spacing using Tailwind scale

### SEO Optimization
- Use semantic HTML5 elements
- Implement proper heading hierarchy (H1 → H2 → H3)
- Add meta tags using next-seo
- Optimize images (WebP/AVIF, lazy loading, alt text)
- Use structured data (JSON-LD) where appropriate
- Ensure fast page load times
- Implement proper canonical URLs

### Blog Post Structure
All blog posts must follow this pattern:
1. Hero section with featured image
2. Title and metadata (author, date, read time)
3. Introduction paragraph
4. Content sections with H2/H3 headings
5. Ad slots (after intro, mid-content, end)
6. Image galleries/sections
7. Call-to-action sections
8. Related posts section

### Ad Placement
- Ads should be non-intrusive
- Place ads after natural content breaks
- Use placeholder components for ad slots
- Ensure ads don't break responsive layout
- Follow Google AdSense best practices

### Performance
- Optimize images (use Next.js Image component)
- Implement lazy loading for below-fold content
- Minimize JavaScript bundle size
- Use dynamic imports for heavy components
- Implement proper caching strategies
- Monitor Core Web Vitals

### Accessibility
- Use proper ARIA labels
- Ensure keyboard navigation
- Maintain color contrast ratios (WCAG AA)
- Provide alt text for all images
- Use semantic HTML elements
- Test with screen readers

### Git Workflow
- Use descriptive commit messages
- Create feature branches for new features
- Keep commits atomic and focused
- Review code before merging

### Testing
- Test on multiple devices and browsers
- Verify responsive breakpoints
- Check SEO metadata
- Validate HTML/CSS
- Test loading performance

## Common Patterns

### Blog Post Component
```typescript
interface BlogPost {
  id: string;
  title: string;
  slug: string;
  excerpt: string;
  content: string;
  featuredImage: string;
  author: string;
  publishedAt: string;
  category: string;
  tags: string[];
  readTime: number;
}
```

### Ad Slot Component
```typescript
interface AdSlotProps {
  position: 'header' | 'sidebar' | 'inline' | 'footer';
  size: 'banner' | 'rectangle' | 'square';
}
```

## Naming Conventions
- Components: PascalCase (e.g., `BlogPost.tsx`)
- Files: kebab-case for pages, PascalCase for components
- Functions: camelCase
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE
- Types/Interfaces: PascalCase with descriptive names

## Dependencies
- Keep dependencies up to date
- Use exact versions in production
- Review and remove unused dependencies
- Prefer well-maintained packages

## Security
- Sanitize user inputs
- Use environment variables for sensitive data
- Implement proper CORS policies
- Validate all external data
- Keep dependencies updated for security patches

## Documentation
- Document complex algorithms
- Add README for setup instructions
- Document API endpoints
- Maintain changelog for major updates

